---
layout: container
title: Joe Masilotti, the Hotwire Native guy.
description: I help Rails developers build web-powered iOS and Android apps with Hotwire Native.
permalink: /
hide_avatar: true
---

<div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-y-16 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-rows-[auto_1fr] lg:gap-y-12">
  <div class="lg:px-20">
    <div class="max-w-[250px] px-2.5 lg:max-w-[300px]">
      <figure>
        <img src="/assets/images/joe.jpg" width="300" height="300" alt="Joe Masilotti" class="aspect-square sm:-rotate-3 rounded-2xl bg-gray-100 object-cover">
        <figcaption class="sr-only">Joe Masilotti</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="lg:row-span-2">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-800 sm:text-5xl">
      <span class="block leading-tight">I'm Joe Masilotti,</span> the <span class="inline-block bg-primary-300/50 italic px-2 py-1 -my-1 -mx-1">Hotwire Native</span> guy!
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-2xl text-gray-600 font-medium">{{ page.description }}</p>
    <div class="mt-6 flex gap-6">
      {% for social in site.data.socials %}
        <a href="{{ social.href }}" target="_blank" title="{{ social.title }}" aria-label="{{ social.title.titleize }}" class="group cursor-pointer -m-1 p-1">
          {% svg "/assets/icons/{{ social.icon }}" class="h-6 w-6 fill-gray-500 transition group-hover:fill-gray-600" %}
        </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-16 md:mt-20 -mx-4">
  <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:justify-center gap-8 py-4">
    {% for offering in site.data.offerings %}
      {% include card.liquid object=offering %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>

{% if site.testimonials %}
  <div class="mt-16 md:mt-20">
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 md:-mx-6">
      {% for testimonial in site.data.testimonials %}
        {% include testimonial.liquid object=testimonial %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
{% endif %}
